Privacy Policy

Last Updated: 29th Sep 2025

Thank you for playing Asteroid Blaster!
Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our mobile game.

1. Information We Collect
a. Personal Information

We do not collect, store, or share any personal information such as your name, email address, phone number, or contact details.

b. Non-Personal Information

To improve gameplay and app performance, we may collect some non-personal data such as:

Device type and operating system version

App performance data (e.g., crashes or bugs)

Gameplay statistics (e.g., high scores, level progress)

This data is collected anonymously and cannot be used to identify you personally.

c. Advertising and Analytics

Asteroid Blaster may display ads from third-party networks (such as Google AdMob or similar).
These ad providers may use cookies or advertising identifiers to show relevant ads and measure performance.

To learn more about how these third parties handle data, please refer to their privacy policies (e.g., Google Privacy Policy
).

2. How We Use Information

Any data we collect is used for the following purposes:

To improve game performance and user experience

To fix bugs and enhance gameplay

To display relevant advertisements

To analyze basic usage trends (e.g., how often players open the app)

3. Children‚Äôs Privacy

Asteroid Blaster is designed for general audiences and does not knowingly collect personal data from children under 13.
If you believe that a child has provided personal data to us, please contact us and we will delete such information promptly.

4. Third-Party Services

The game may use third-party services such as:

Ad networks (for showing ads)

Analytics tools (to understand app performance)

These third parties may collect data in accordance with their own privacy policies.
We encourage you to review those policies before using the game.

5. Data Security

We take reasonable measures to protect your data from unauthorized access or misuse.
However, please note that no method of electronic storage or transmission over the internet is 100% secure.

